# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# EmailJS Configuration
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Create a free account at https://www.emailjs.com
# 2. Create an Email Service (e.g. Gmail, Outlook) and copy the Service ID
# 3. Create an Email Template and copy the Template ID
# 4. Copy your Public Key from Account → API Keys
#
# Rename this file to .env and fill in your values.
# IMPORTANT: Never commit your .env file to version control.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=service_xxxxxxx
VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=template_xxxxxxx
VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Google Analytics 4 (optional — analytics disabled if unset)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Create a GA4 property + Web data stream at https://analytics.google.com
# and copy the Measurement ID from the stream details (format: G-XXXXXXXXXX).
VITE_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX
